5000|$|In optical communications, {{intensity}} modulation (IM) {{is a form}} of modulation in which the optical power output of a source is varied in accordance with some characteristic of the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal.</b> The envelope of the <b>modulated</b> optical <b>signal</b> is an analog of the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> {{in the sense that the}} instantaneous power of the envelope is an analog of the characteristic of interest in the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal.</b>|$|R
