40|$|Method and {{apparatus}} {{is presented}} for producing a phase-modulated waveform having {{a high degree}} of linearity between the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> and the phase of the <b>modulated</b> carrier <b>signal.</b> Two signals representing finite odd and even power series transformations of the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> are produced and multiplied with two quadrature components of the input carrier signal, respectively. One of the multiplied signals is subtracted from the other and the resulting signal is hard-limited to produce a phase-modulated output signal. The means for producing the two signals representing the odd and even power series of the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> includes means for varying the coefficients of the two power series. By means of an existing computer program, the coefficients of the two power series are selected such that there is an extremely high degree of linearity between the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> and the phase of the <b>modulated</b> carrier <b>signal...</b>|$|R
