25|$|Many PLL {{frequency}} synthesizers {{can also}} generate frequency modulation (FM). The <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> {{is added to}} the output of the loop filter, directly varying the frequency of the VCO and the synthesizer output. The modulation will also appear at the phase comparator output, reduced in amplitude by any frequency division. Any spectral components in the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal</b> too low to be blocked by the loop filter end up back at the VCO input with opposite polarity to the <b>modulating</b> <b>signal,</b> thus canceling them out. (The loop effectively sees these components as VCO noise to be tracked out.) Modulation components above the loop filter cutoff frequency cannot return to the VCO input so they remain in the VCO output.|$|R
